import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    country_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Airports')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=480, height=480).generate(text)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
